    "402208": {
        "Desc": "Discuss how to deal with the All-Devouring Narwhal",
        "Talk": [
            [
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "That was way too close! How did that thing just burst into the opera house!? Wait. Was that the huge whale you saw in your dream?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "That's right."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "I'd wager that it's also the one that Childe saw when he was young."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "So, we've met it at last... I understand very well why it has chosen to make an appearance here."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "That \"whale\" does not belong to Teyvat. It is a monster that has traversed the stars, weeping all the while."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "It has been greedily consuming the energy from the planet's Primordial Sea, using it to grow. That is the main cause for the rising sea levels..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "And once it has finished consuming all of the energy contained within the Sea, its next step will be..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Clorinde",
                    "T": "You said that when the Hydro Archon first created Fontainians out of Oceanids, she filled their blood vessels with Primordial Seawater..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "Precisely. That whale finds the \"blood\" of Fontainians nigh impossible to resist."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "Therefore, when it left the Primordial Sea, it decided to make its next stop a packed opera house full of food — food in the form of Fontainians."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Navia",
                    "T": "We just barely managed to push it back, right? In that case... Won't it come back to target the people again once it's managed to recover its strength?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "That is correct. Indeed, it is more accurate to say that we should thank that Harbinger for buying us some time. Without him, the whale would have likely come onto land far sooner."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "From the way he looked, he must have been fighting the creature for quite a long time."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "That battle maniac... We've always known that he had a special connection with that whale, but we definitely didn't expect it to help us out like this."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "Anyway, now that we know that this whale is the actual cause of the disaster recorded in the prophecy, all we need to do to stop the prophecy would be to find a way to beat it up, right?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "It is too late..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "What do you mean?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "It had already absorbed too much of the Primordial Sea's energy before we could notice it. At this point, it has become practically integrated with the Sea itself."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Neuvillette",
                    "T": "Even if the entirety of Teyvat were to be destroyed, it could still survive, and swim off towards some other world."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Navia",
                    "T": "That... That's not something I will accept."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Navia",
                    "T": "We've already done everything we can, and we even found the true culprit..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Navia",
                    "T": "We've come so far! You can't just tell me that the last hurdle is some impossible foe. That's just not fair."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Lyney",
                    "T": "Indeed. That's not how a grand performance should end."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Clorinde",
                    "T": "I'll fight it to the end. No matter what."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_1005",
                    "T": "So the prophecy will be fulfilled no matter what, huh..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "..."
                },
                {
                    "N": "Mage \"N\"",
                    "T": "The prophecy... Yes, what has been prophesized will be fulfilled. You may view such things as \"the history of the future.\""
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(After everything, it still turned out like this... We couldn't fight against fate.)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(Wait, but if this is all about fate...)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Mage \"N\"",
                    "T": "Just as prophecies are usually only the future as seen from the perspectives of the gods, could things be happening in hidden corners where the gods' gaze does not fall?"
                },
                {
                    "N": "Mage \"N\"",
                    "T": "Ultimately, fate shall serve as your only guide no matter what will happen in Teyvat's future. All you need to do is to play your part."
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(Could it be... That even if the prophecy will be fulfilled, there will still be a way to save everyone?)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(Did I... miss something...?)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(Wait, I forgot about Furina! What was it that she wanted to say to me at that last moment, in the Giant Magic Box?)"
                },
                {
                    "N": "_0",
                    "T": "(What is her real secret?)"
                }
            ]
        ]
    },
